data.description: Located in one of Carrollton's most sought after neighborhoods on a peaceful cul-de-sac, this Mill Pond home offers fresh paint and low-maintenance luxury vinyl flooring on all 3 levels.  You will notice that the tray ceiling in the dining room and arched doorways are lovely touches as you step into the home. The morning sun brightens the open-concept, kitchen/living room combination. It is a charming spot to enjoy the fireplace on cozy evenings. A quaint 1/2 bath is located near the laundry room, just inside from the 2 car garage with workshop/storage closet. The sunset views from the airy, aesthetic upstairs landing are often stunning. The spacious primary bedroom just off the landing is elegant with double doors, tray ceilings, two walk-in closets, and a sitting room. The adjoining, roomy bathroom is outfitted with a double vanity, oversized soaking tub, and separate shower. Also off of the landing are 2 nicely appointed bedrooms and a full bath. Making your way to the basement, you notice the unique detail of ledges in the stairwell.  As you enter the basement, there are 2 storage closets, as well as a Safe Room. There is ample room in the basement living room to enjoy gatherings, games, or the favored "movie night".  Anyone would enjoy the large bedroom with walk-in closet and full bath in the basement. From the basement living room, you will step into a large backyard with established raised containers to grow your favorite vegetables, herbs or flowers for some garden therapy.  The wide deck is a great location to enjoy the outdoor living space as well!  One of the best features of this home is the annual savings the owner has been able to pocket since installing the solar panels.  The open concept living, crisp bright space, and savings on utilities are all excellent reasons to love this home in an incredible location.  Oh! and did I mention the amenities...including community pool and tennis court?  You will love those too!!
